### 10. **Testing of the Role of Proprioception**
   - **Why it matters**: The study aimed to determine whether **proprioception** (the sense of body position) was responsible for the **aftereffect**.
   - **How VR helps**: The VR headset allows researchers to **simulate the perception of slant using proprioception** without physical contact, which is essential for testing the **role of proprioception**.
   - **Example**: In **Experiment 3**, participants adapted to a "slant" by holding their hands in mid-air (no haptic feedback), and the VR headset was used to guide their hand positions. This setup allowed the researchers to test whether **proprioception** (the 
