### Summary
The VR headset is a powerful tool for understanding haptic slant adaptation because it allows researchers to **simulate the perception of slant without physical contact**, **control the environment precisely**, and **isolate the role of proprioceptive 
information** from haptic feedback. This makes it an ideal tool for studying whether haptic slant adaptation is based on **proprioceptive information** or **haptic feedback**, and whether it is **bimanual** or **unimanual**.
